[5] Venezuela: 1st case, imported
Date: Sun 12 Jun 2020
Source: Infoabe [in Spanish trans, Mod. TY, edited]
https://www.infobae.com/america/agencias/2022/06/12/venezuela-reporta-su-primer-caso-de-viruela-del-mono/


Venezuela has detected its 1st case of monkeypox in a traveler coming from Spain as stated this Sunday [12 Jun 2022] by the Ministry of Health in an announcement.

"By means of an epidemiological fence, the 1st suspected case of monkeypox was detected in the Simon Bolivar International Airport in Maiquetia (24 km [15 mi] from Caracas)" the document stated.

"The patient, who arrived in the country from Madrid, Spain, had contact with 2 infected individuals in Barcelona in that European city. He was immediately isolated, relevant examinations were done, samples taken with positive results, and he is in stable health condition", was added.

The Health Ministry did not provide details about the infected person.

