[6] Brazil (Minas Gerais)
Date: Tue 14 Jun 2022
Source: Play Crazy Game [edited]
https://playcrazygame.com/2022/06/14/ituiutaba-registers-the-second-suspected-case-of-monkeypox-in-minas/


The state of Minas Gerais is investigating a 2nd suspected case of monkeypox. The case was registered in Ituiutaba. The 1st suspected case in Minas is being investigated in Uberl√¢ndia.

According to the Minas Gerais State Health Department (SES-MG), the agency received, in the early evening of Monday (13 Jun 2022), the notification of this suspected case of the disease verified in Ituiutaba. The secretariat was informed by the Pontal City Hall this Sunday (12 Jun 2022]).

The state has not yet released details about the suspected case in Ituiutaba. There is currently no information about the patient's age and occupation. But it has already been reported by the Ituiutaba City Hall that it is a man, who presented some of the symptoms of the disease and sought care last Sunday (12 Jun 2022).

The Municipal Health Department said that the patient is in good health and is in isolation at home, being monitored by the Department of Health Surveillance.

The 1st suspected case of monkeypox in Minas, registered in Uberl√¢ndia and which is being investigated by SES-MG, was a patient who was hospitalized at the Uberl√¢ndia Medical Center (UMC) hospital and who died in the last week.

The patient was a 41-year-old criminal police officer who lived in Araguari and worked in Uberl√¢ndia. According to the Center for Strategic Information on Health Surveillance (CIEVS-Minas), suspected cases of the disease reported in Uberl√¢ndia and Ituiutaba have no history of displacement or travel abroad.

It was also informed that, in both cases, among the close contacts of both -- who are being monitored --, there is still no symptomatic case of the disease.

The SES-MG advised that samples from the patients of the 2 suspected cases verified in the state were to be collected for analysis by the Ezequiel Dias Foundation (Funed). The samples were collected and sent to the Foundation.

The 1st case of monkeypox in the country was confirmed last Thursday (9 Jun 2022). He is a 41-year-old resident of S√£o Paulo (capital), who recently traveled to Spain. He is hospitalized at the Instituto de Infectologia Em√≠lio Ribas, in good clinical condition.

This Saturday (11 Jun 2022), the S√£o Paulo State Department of Health confirmed the 2nd case of monkeypox in Brazil. This is a 29-year-old man who traveled to Europe in recent weeks and is isolated at his home in Vinhedo, in the interior of S√£o Paulo.

A 3rd case of the disease was also confirmed this weekend [11-12 Jun 2022]. This is a patient in the state of Rio Grande do Sul.

